Man develops, perfecta or depraves, but he creates nothing. The scientific golden mean commended by Py· thagoras, consists therefore, in seizing the principles of the sciences where they are and developing them freely without being constrained or driven by any false ideas. As to that which concerns morals, it is forcibly enough expressed by all that has preceded.
